                  July 15 (Bloomberg) --Plenum Investments AG, a Zurich-based
money manager, hired  Stefan Meisser  this month as a portfolio
manager to trade European power and carbon emissions, the
company said.  
 Meisser joined Plenum from the Swiss office of Imarex ASAâ€™s
Nena unit, an energy-market research company.  
